---
/**
 * Homepage — the project's own front door, set in its own voice.
 *
 * Design Field Card identity, applied to ourselves: warm paper + ink, forest
 * green primary, a single coral accent; monospace editorial eyebrows, numbered
 * moves, hairline rules. Manual §0 (deference — the words lead, no spectacle),
 * §7.3 (colour only via tokens), §7.4 (no glass off-chrome), §7.5 (calm motion),
 * §7.6 (WCAG 2.2 AA). Voice: the way a trusted neighbour would say it.
 *
 * The hero's right column is a "blueprint specimen" — a static artifact that
 * shows the Studio thinking, in our own type system. That is the illustration;
 * there is no clip-art, no stock people, no gradient glow.
 */
---

<style is:global>
  /* Splash home only. Collapse Starlight's docs PageTitle so the page reads as a
     landing, not an article; keep #_top as the skip-link target. */
  .main-pane > main > .content-panel:first-child { padding: 0; border: 0; }
  .main-pane > main > .content-panel:first-child h1#_top {
    position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; padding: 0; margin: -1px;
    overflow: hidden; clip: rect(0 0 0 0); white-space: nowrap; border: 0;
  }
  .main-pane > main > .content-panel + .content-panel { border-top: 0; }
  .main-pane > main > .content-panel .sl-container { max-width: none; }
  /* A front door, not a docs search page: hide the header search on home only
     (search stays on every other page, and Ctrl/Cmd-K still works here). */
  .header button[data-open-modal] { display: none; }
</style>

<div class="wcb-landing">
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'WebSite',
    name: 'We Can Just Build Things',
    url: 'https://wecanjustbuildthings.dev',
    description:
      'A verified, values-enforced catalog and guided build flow for shipping community tools with AI agents — never on Meta, OpenAI, or xAI.',
  })} />

  {/* ============================= HERO ============================= */}
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="wcb-eyebrow">For people who know their community — not how to code</p>
      <h1 id="hero-title">We can just build things — for the people who need them.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        You know your people, and what they need. Tell the Build Studio in plain
        words, and an AI agent builds it — only on foundations we've already
        checked and locked to your values. <b>You bring the wisdom; it brings the
        hands.</b>
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/build/">
          Open the Build Studio
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a class="btn btn-quiet" href="#how">See how it works</a>
      </div>
      <ul class="trust" aria-label="What you can count on">
        <li><span class="mk" aria-hidden="true">◆</span> No Meta · OpenAI · xAI</li>
        <li><span class="mk" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> License-verified at a commit</li>
        <li><span class="mk" aria-hidden="true">★</span> 1,300+ vetted tools</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    {/* Blueprint specimen — a Studio artifact, in our own type system. */}
    <figure class="specimen" aria-label="An example of what the Build Studio gives back">
      <figcaption class="spec-head">
        <span class="wcb-eyebrow">Build Studio</span>
        <span class="spec-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      </figcaption>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span class="spec-label">You said</span>
        <p class="spec-said">“A map of the free fridges in our neighbourhood — in Spanish and English.”</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span class="spec-label">Your blueprint</span>
        <ul class="spec-stack">
          <li><span class="ok" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> <b>Leaflet</b> — the map <span class="lic">MIT</span></li>
          <li><span class="ok" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> <b>MapLibre</b> — open tiles <span class="lic">BSD-3</span></li>
          <li><span class="ok" aria-hidden="true">✓</span> <b>Nostr</b> — sync across phones <span class="lic">MIT</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="spec-foot"><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Values-locked — nothing from Meta, OpenAI, or xAI</p>
    </figure>
  </section>

  {/* ========================= HOW IT WORKS ========================= */}
  <section class="band" id="how" aria-labelledby="how-title">
    <p class="wcb-eyebrow">From your words to a working tool</p>
    <h2 id="how-title" class="band-title">Three moves, and you stay the director</h2>
    <ol class="moves">
      <li class="move">
        <span class="num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
        <div class="move-body">
          <h3>Describe it</h3>
          <p>Tell the Studio what you're building, the way you'd explain it to a
            friend. No tech words, no jargon — just what your community needs to do.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="move">
        <span class="num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
        <div class="move-body">
          <h3>Get the blueprint</h3>
          <p>It comes back with the exact tools for the job and a plan in plain
            language — every piece license-checked, nothing owned by Meta, OpenAI,
            or xAI.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="move">
        <span class="num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
        <div class="move-body">
          <h3>Build it together</h3>
          <p>Hand the plan to your AI agent. You direct; it does the work — and you
            ship something your community will feel was made <em>by us, for us</em>.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  {/* =========================== MENTOR ============================ */}
  <section class="mentor" aria-labelledby="mentor-title">
    <p class="wcb-eyebrow">You don't have to be a developer. Or a designer.</p>
    <h2 id="mentor-title">You have something rarer: you know your people.</h2>
    <p>
      The elders, the kids, the crew, the folks on five-year-old phones in bright
      sun — that knowledge is the most important design input there is, and no
      big-tech default has it. The Studio carries the technical rules and the
      accessibility floor; you bring the judgment.
    </p>
    <p class="pull">You bring the wisdom. The agent brings the hands.</p>
    <a class="link-arrow" href="/guides/design-for-your-community/">
      Read the Design Field Guide
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
    </a>
  </section>

  {/* ====================== WHY YOU CAN TRUST IT ==================== */}
  <section class="band" aria-labelledby="trust-title">
    <p class="wcb-eyebrow">Why this is different</p>
    <h2 id="trust-title" class="band-title">Built to be trusted — and to last</h2>
    <div class="points">
      <div class="point">
        <h3><span class="lead-word">Values, enforced</span> — not promised.</h3>
        <p>Nothing in your stack is owned by Meta, OpenAI, or xAI. You don't have
          to take our word for it — we re-check it on every single build.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="point">
        <h3><span class="lead-word">Trust you can see.</span></h3>
        <p>Every tool is license-verified at a real commit, with the receipt
          attached. The catalog, the method, and the enforcement are all open.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="point">
        <h3><span class="lead-word">Everyone's invited.</span></h3>
        <p>Every build starts at the WCAG 2.2 AA floor — readable, tappable,
          screen-reader friendly — so no one in your community is left out.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="point">
        <h3><span class="lead-word">Built to outlast.</span></h3>
        <p>Open methodology, open catalog, open enforcement — made with
          communities, so it keeps working when people move on.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* =========================== CLOSING =========================== */}
  <section class="closing" aria-label="Where to go next">
    <div class="doors">
      <a class="door" href="/start/">
        <span class="wcb-eyebrow">New here?</span>
        <b>Start in three minutes <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></b>
        <span class="door-sub">A gentle walk from idea to your first build.</span>
      </a>
      <a class="door" href="/catalog/">
        <span class="wcb-eyebrow">Know your stack?</span>
        <b>Browse 1,300+ vetted tools <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></b>
        <span class="door-sub">Every one license-checked and values-clean.</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <p class="signoff">We can just build things — <span class="well">well.</span></p>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
  .wcb-landing {
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: clamp(var(--wcb-space-xl), 7vw, 5rem);
    color: var(--wcb-ink);
  }

  /* ---------------------------- HERO ---------------------------- */
  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 0.95fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(var(--wcb-space-lg), 4vw, var(--wcb-space-xl));
    padding-top: clamp(var(--wcb-space-md), 4vw, var(--wcb-space-xl));
  }
  .hero-copy .wcb-eyebrow { margin: 0 0 var(--wcb-space-sm); display: block; }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.2vw, 3.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--wcb-ink);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .lead {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.7vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--wcb-ink-soft);
    max-width: 38ch;
    margin: var(--wcb-space-md) 0 0;
  }
  .lead b { color: var(--wcb-ink); font-weight: 700; }

  .actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--wcb-space-sm); margin-top: var(--wcb-space-lg); }
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--wcb-space-2xs);
    min-height: 2.875rem; /* 46px tap target */
    padding: 0 var(--wcb-space-md);
    border-radius: var(--wcb-radius-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--wcb-text-base);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      transform var(--wcb-motion-fast) var(--wcb-easing-standard),
      background var(--wcb-motion-fast) var(--wcb-easing-standard),
      border-color var(--wcb-motion-fast) var(--wcb-easing-standard);
  }
  .btn svg { width: 1.05rem; height: 1.05rem; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--wcb-green); color: var(--wcb-on-accent); }
  .btn-primary:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--wcb-green) 88%, black); }
  .btn-primary:active { transform: translateY(0); }
  .btn-quiet { color: var(--wcb-ink); border: 1px solid var(--wcb-line); background: transparent; }
  .btn-quiet:hover { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--wcb-green) 9%, transparent); border-color: var(--wcb-green); }

  .trust {
    list-style: none;
    margin: var(--wcb-space-lg) 0 0;
    padding: var(--wcb-space-sm) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--wcb-line);
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--wcb-space-2xs) var(--wcb-space-md);
    font-size: var(--wcb-text-sm);
    color: var(--wcb-ink-soft);
  }
  .trust li { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--wcb-space-3xs); }
  .trust .mk { color: var(--wcb-green); font-weight: 700; }

  /* Blueprint specimen */
  .specimen {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--wcb-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--wcb-line);
    border-radius: var(--wcb-radius-md);
    padding: var(--wcb-space-md);
  }
  .spec-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding-bottom: var(--wcb-space-2xs);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--wcb-ink);
  }
  .spec-dot { width: 0.6rem; height: 0.6rem; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--wcb-green); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--wcb-green) 22%, transparent); }
  .spec-row { padding: var(--wcb-space-sm) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--wcb-line); }
  .spec-label {
    font-family: var(--sl-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--wcb-text-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--wcb-ink-soft);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--wcb-space-3xs);
  }
  .spec-said { margin: 0; font-size: var(--wcb-text-base); color: var(--wcb-ink); line-height: 1.45; }
  .spec-stack { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--wcb-space-2xs); }
  .spec-stack li { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: var(--wcb-space-2xs); font-size: var(--wcb-text-sm); color: var(--wcb-ink-soft); }
  .spec-stack b { color: var(--wcb-ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .spec-stack .ok { color: var(--wcb-green); font-weight: 800; }
  .spec-stack .lic { margin-left: auto; font-family: var(--sl-font-mono); font-size: var(--wcb-text-xs); color: var(--wcb-ink-soft); }
  .spec-foot {
    margin: var(--wcb-space-sm) 0 0;
    font-size: var(--wcb-text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--wcb-green);
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--wcb-space-3xs);
    align-items: center;
  }

  /* --------------------- shared band heading -------------------- */
  .band-title, .mentor h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.2vw, 2.2rem);
    line-height: 1.12;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: var(--wcb-space-2xs) 0 0;
    border: 0;
    padding: 0;
    color: var(--wcb-ink);
    max-width: 24ch;
  }
  .band > .wcb-eyebrow, .mentor > .wcb-eyebrow { display: block; }

  /* ------------------------ HOW IT WORKS ------------------------ */
  .moves {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--wcb-space-lg) 0 0;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--wcb-ink);
  }
  .move {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3.5rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--wcb-space-md);
    padding: var(--wcb-space-md) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--wcb-line);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .move .num { font-family: var(--sl-font-mono); font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--wcb-green); line-height: 1; }
  .move h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 var(--wcb-space-3xs); color: var(--wcb-ink); }
  .move p { margin: 0; color: var(--wcb-ink-soft); max-width: 56ch; line-height: 1.55; }
  .move em { font-style: italic; color: var(--wcb-ink); }

  /* --------------------------- MENTOR --------------------------- */
  .mentor {
    padding: clamp(var(--wcb-space-lg), 4vw, 2.5rem);
    background: var(--wcb-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--wcb-line);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--wcb-green);
    border-radius: var(--wcb-radius-sm);
  }
  .mentor p { margin: var(--wcb-space-md) 0 0; font-size: var(--wcb-text-lg); line-height: 1.55; color: var(--wcb-ink-soft); max-width: 60ch; }
  .mentor .pull {
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.2vw, 1.5rem);
    line-height: 1.35;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--wcb-ink);
    max-width: none;
  }
  .link-arrow {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--wcb-space-3xs);
    margin-top: var(--wcb-space-md);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--wcb-coral-text);
  }
  .link-arrow svg { width: 1.05rem; height: 1.05rem; transition: transform var(--wcb-motion-standard) var(--wcb-easing-standard); }
  .link-arrow:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .link-arrow:hover svg { transform: translateX(4px); }

  /* ----------------------- TRUST POINTS ------------------------ */
  .points {
    margin-top: var(--wcb-space-lg);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--wcb-space-lg) var(--wcb-space-xl);
  }
  .point h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 var(--wcb-space-2xs);
    padding-top: var(--wcb-space-2xs);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--wcb-coral);
    color: var(--wcb-ink);
  }
  .point .lead-word { color: var(--wcb-coral-text); }
  .point p { margin: 0; color: var(--wcb-ink-soft); line-height: 1.55; }

  /* -------------------------- CLOSING -------------------------- */
  .doors { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--wcb-space-sm); }
  .door {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--wcb-space-3xs);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: var(--wcb-space-md);
    background: var(--wcb-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--wcb-line);
    border-radius: var(--wcb-radius-sm);
    transition:
      transform var(--wcb-motion-standard) var(--wcb-easing-standard),
      border-color var(--wcb-motion-standard) var(--wcb-easing-standard);
  }
  .door:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); border-color: var(--wcb-green); }
  .door b { color: var(--wcb-ink); font-size: 1.15rem; }
  .door-sub { font-size: var(--wcb-text-sm); color: var(--wcb-ink-soft); }
  .signoff { text-align: center; margin: var(--wcb-space-md) 0 0; font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.9rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--wcb-ink); }
  .signoff .well { color: var(--wcb-coral-text); }

  /* ------------------------ responsive ------------------------ */
  @media (max-width: 50rem) {
    .hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .specimen { order: 2; }
    .points { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--wcb-space-md); }
    .doors { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .btn, .door, .link-arrow svg { transition: none; }
  }
</style>
